snippet.title: Wish | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Be careful what you wish for ‚≠êÔ∏è Watch the NEW trailer for Disney's #Wish, coming only to theaters this Thanksgiving. 

Revealed today are additional members of the film‚Äôs voice cast, who join previously announced cast members Ariana DeBose, who voices 17-year-old heroine Asha; Chris Pine, who lends his voice to the formidable King Magnifico; and Alan Tudyk, who provides the memorable voice of Asha‚Äôs pet goat, Valentino. 

Cast members include:
Angelique Cabral as Queen Amaya, the wife and sounding board of King Magnifico; Victor Garber as Asha‚Äôs grandfather, Sabino, who‚Äîat 100 years old‚Äîis patiently waiting for his wish to be granted; and Natasha Rothwell as Asha‚Äôs loving and supportive mom, Sakina.
 
Plus, Asha‚Äôs tight-knit group of confidants, protectors and forever friends: Jennifer Kumiyama as Asha‚Äôs dearest friend, Dahlia, who‚Äôs an accomplished baker and unofficial leader of their group; Evan Peters as the strong guy with a big heart and bigger yawn, Simon; Harvey Guill√©n as Gabo, who may be cynical, but he has a heart of gold; Ramy Youssef as Safi, who‚Äôs plagued by allergies; Niko Vargas as Asha‚Äôs joyful, always smiling buddy, Hal; Della Saba as the seemingly shy teenager, Bazeema, who‚Äôs full of surprises; and Jon Rudnitsky as Asha‚Äôs rosy-cheeked, wiggly-eared pal, Dario.
